title: Hartogs phenomenon and the problem of complex spheres
abstract: In this paper, we solve the following problem : Is there any complex structure on the sphere S^6?

title: Left Cauchy-Riemann operator. l H and Dolbeault-Grothendieck lemma on the group of Heisenberg type H-n(B)(C)
abstract: We extend to differential forms the system of partial differential equations <(partial derivative(l)(H))over bar> u = f defined for functions as follows {partial derivative u/partial derivative(z) over bar (j) + i/4 Sigma(k=1) (k=n-m) (partial derivative Bk/partial derivative(z) over bar (j) partial derivative u/partial derivative zeta(k) + partial derivative(B) over bar (k)/partial derivative(z) over bar (j) partial derivative u/partial derivative(zeta) over bar (k)) - fj 1 <= j <= m, partial derivative u/partial derivative(zeta) over bar (k) = f(m+k) 1 <= k <= n - m. This leads to the <(partial derivative(l)(H))over bar>-cohomology, and then we will prove the corresponding Dolbeault-Grothendieck lemma.
